{
  "stem": "14613.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The composition of the school, really, as to-- OK-- consisted basically-- we went to school basically six times a week.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And because of our dual-teaching program, we went to school-- I don't remember, 8 o'clock or 9 o'clock.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And [BACKGROUND NOISE] we studied until about 3 o'clock, 4 o'clock.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So that, in a way, it was a full day of schooling.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And also, we went six days a week.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "If I were to compare it-- which I did go for one year to school in the United States-- it was much more difficult.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And it took much more time and effort to, to, to, to, to go to school, to study, and, of course, to be a good teacher-- a good student, much more than in the United States.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When I went to school, I have no favorite subject.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The favorite subjects was to have none.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The favorite subjects would be to go [LAUGHS] play soccer, play volleyball, play basketball.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "This would be my favorite subject.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So if I go back and recall what they were, this [LAUGHS] is what they were-- the gymnastic was my favorite subject, I would say.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But, but in spite of that, we were very good students, so that we did apply ourselves.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And it was implied that we should be good students.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So, so we did.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We were brought up, which you can call, in-- more in the Jewish tradition, rather than in the religious life.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We did not go, by and large, to the synagogue Fridays or Saturdays.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We did go with our father.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And here the-- also the distinction.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The boys went with the father to the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "My mother went, sometimes, with the girls to the other-- to another synagogue.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
